<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="54">
Li (1979) regarded 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Triplophysa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuis">T. tenuis (Day)</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Triplophysa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkae">T. stoliczkae</taxonomicName>
, but Wu et al (1999) regarded it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Triplophysa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuicauda">T. tenuicauda (Steindachner 1866)</taxonomicName>
. We are inclined to support Wuâ€™s view on the basis of the round caudal peduncle, dorsal fin origin position and thick lips, but the status of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Nemacheilidae" genus="Triplophysa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuis">T. tenuis</taxonomicName>
requires more study, especially its type material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
